    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix parse_cgmr() function return value inconsistency\n\n### Summary\nThe `parse_cgmr()` function in at_command.c was returning the command ID instead of RETURNok, causing unexpected behavior when called directly. This change modifies both `parse_cgmr()` and `parse_cgmr_test()` to return RETURNok on success to match expected calling conventions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_command.c`: Modified parse_cgmr() and parse_cgmr_test() to return RETURNok instead of at_command->id\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling parse_cgmr() directly with valid parameters, the function would return AT_CGMR (value 4) instead of RETURNok (value 0), causing calling code that expects standard return codes to incorrectly interpret the success status. This led to inconsistent behavior compared to other AT command parsers that follow the RETURNok/RETURNerror pattern.\n\nUsers reported that after calling parse_cgmr(), their code path would incorrectly treat the successful parsing as an error condition due to the non-zero return value, even though the at_command structure was properly populated.\n"
}